Glossary of Genetic Terms

[-- single nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) --]

defined:     Common, but minute, variations that occur in human DNA at a
             frequency of one every 1,000 bases. These variations can be used to
             track inheritance in families. SNP is pronounced "snip".
explained:   Listen to a detailed explanation.
             Dr. Francis Collins, director of the National Human Genome Research
             Institute, defines single nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs).
related
terms:       deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA), inherited, nucleotide,
             polymorphism, genetic code (ATGC)
